I"Ø<p>Cablegram unnumbered, 30 September 1937</p>

<p>Your telegram 29th September [1]</p>

<p>Desire you accept any invitation for Australia to join Sub- committee.</p>

<p>Resolution of moral condemnation on bombing of open towns by Japanese aircraft widely regarded as justifiable and feeling in Australia is hardening against ruthless nature of Japanese aggression.</p>

<p>LYONS</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 Document 69.</p>

<p>_</p>

<p><em>[AA : A981, CHINA 114, ix]</em></p>
